---
// One idea: the body stops being a machine that keeps breaking and becomes a sea
// you're learning to sail.
---
<svg width="560" height="180" viewBox="0 0 560 180" role="img" aria-labelledby="ss2-t">
  <title id="ss2-t">On the left, the body drawn as a broken machine — a cracked gear, faded. On the right, the body drawn as a sea with waves, a small boat sailing its swells with a spirit of adventure rather than fighting them.</title>
  <!-- body as broken machine -->
  <circle class="ink hair" cx="90" cy="80" r="30" opacity="0.55" />
  <g class="ink hair" opacity="0.55"><path d="M90 50 L 90 42 M90 118 L 90 110 M60 80 L 52 80 M120 80 L 128 80 M69 59 L 63 53 M111 59 L 117 53" /></g>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M78 68 L 102 92 M102 68 L 78 92" stroke="var(--poppy)" opacity="0.6" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="52" y="140" font-size="13" opacity="0.65">a machine that breaks</text>
  <!-- body as a sea to sail -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M320 96 C 344 78, 366 114, 392 96 C 418 78, 440 114, 466 96 C 492 78, 512 106, 528 96" stroke="var(--canopy-deep)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M360 112 C 384 98, 406 124, 432 108" opacity="0.5" />
  <path class="ink block" d="M406 82 C 424 82, 452 82, 466 82 C 462 92, 452 98, 438 98 C 424 98, 412 90, 406 82 Z" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M436 82 L 436 62 L 452 74" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="440" cy="70" r="3" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="336" y="140" font-size="13">a sea you&rsquo;re learning to sail</text>
</svg>
